miniTEM-T1 default: Tier 1 if generic SOPs for sample preparation and image evaluation are used.
miniTEM-T2 default: Performance comparable to standard TEM (Tier 2) if sample preparation and image evaluation is optimised for each material.
BET default: This measurement technique may not yield reliable results if the material to be analysed shows porous properties or severe states of aggregation/agglomeration. As per the updated EC nanomaterial definition recommendation, the particle type shape is no longer a crucial criterion for the analysis. A VSSA < 6 will result in a non-nanomaterial decision while a VSSA above or equal to this threshold suggests a potential nanomaterial for which further analysis is suggested.
